- Use `spring-boot-starter-batch` for batch processing.
- Configure batch in `application.properties` or `application.yml`.
- Set `spring.batch.job.enabled=false` to disable default job execution.
- Use `@EnableBatchProcessing` annotation in main class.
- Implement `ItemReader`, `ItemProcessor`, and `ItemWriter` interfaces.
- Use `JdbcBatchItemWriter` for batch inserts with Spring Data JPA.
- Configure `batchSize` in writer properties.
- Example:
  ```java
  @Bean
  public JdbcBatchItemWriter<MyEntity> writer(DataSource dataSource) {
      JdbcBatchItemWriter<MyEntity> writer = new JdbcBatchItemWriter<>();
      writer.setItemSqlParameterSourceProvider(new BeanPropertyItemSqlParameterSourceProvider<>());
      writer.setSql("INSERT INTO my_table (column1, column2) VALUES (:column1, :column2)");
      writer.setDataSource(dataSource);
      return writer;
  }
  ```
- Use `@StepScope` for step-specific beans.
- Configure transaction management with `@Transactional`.
- Monitor batch jobs using Spring Boot Actuator.
